item.title: Is anyone else getting this stupid warning bullshit in chrome
item.dc:creator: @z z
item.description:
@z wrote:

[quote=“Moparisthebest, post:8, topic:441374”]It’s the latest version of chrome, blocking the google ads by default instead of the former behavior of chrome (and the current behavior of firefox) which is just to warn the user and display the ads anyway. Google has yet to comment on this, but it is killing sites that are funded by ad income but also wish to provide a secure way to browse their sites. I currently don’t know of any workaround to avoid this, but I will turn off the functionality that forces you to stay on HTTPS once you visit a link.[/quote]Damn, nice find. I’d much appreciate that, thank you.

Read full topic

item.title: Is anyone else getting this stupid warning bullshit in chrome
item.dc:creator: @moparisthebest Moparisthebest
item.description:
@moparisthebest wrote:

It’s the latest version of chrome, blocking the google ads by default instead of the former behavior of chrome (and the current behavior of firefox) which is just to warn the user and display the ads anyway. Google has yet to comment on this, but it is killing sites that are funded by ad income but also wish to provide a secure way to browse their sites. I currently don’t know of any workaround to avoid this, but I will turn off the functionality that forces you to stay on HTTPS once you visit a link.
